---
import PrivacyDoc from '@/layouts/PrivacyDoc.astro';
import { apps } from '@/data/apps';

const app = apps.find((a) => a.id === 'math-sprint')!;
---

<PrivacyDoc app={app}>
  <p>Math Sprint is a local, offline-first practice app for math and memory.</p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>Math Sprint does not collect personal information from users.</p>
  <p>
    Math Sprint does not require account creation and does not ask users to provide name, email
    address, phone number, location, contacts, photos, or payment information.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Stored on the Device</h2>
  <p>
    Math Sprint stores limited app data only on the user's device so the app can work offline and
    show personal progress features.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>App settings such as language, haptics, sound, and high contrast mode preferences</li>
    <li>Game mode and difficulty</li>
    <li>Score, correct answer count, total question count, elapsed time, and bonus points</li>
    <li>Date and time of play</li>
    <li>Daily challenge completion history and streak state</li>
    <li>Local analytics event logs used for product debugging and future local analysis</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This information is stored locally on the device and is not sent to our servers.</p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>Math Sprint does not sell, share, or transfer user data to third parties.</p>

  <h2>Internet and Network Use</h2>
  <p>
    Math Sprint is designed to work without creating user accounts or sending gameplay data to a
    backend service. At this time, Math Sprint does not transmit personal data to us or to third
    parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    Math Sprint is intended for general practice gameplay and may be used by children. We do not
    knowingly collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    Because gameplay history is stored locally on the device, users can clear app data or uninstall
    the app to remove that stored data.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    If this privacy policy changes, the updated version will be posted with a new effective date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Developer: Enes</p>
  <p>Package name: <code>com.enesk6u.mathsprint</code></p>
  <p>Contact email: <code>enesk6u@gmail.com</code></p>
</PrivacyDoc>
